3. Develop models: Use MATLAB to develop models that represent the transportation system and its interactions with population density. You can use tools such as SimMechanics, SimEvents, and Stateflow to create simulations of traffic flow, public transit systems, and other transportation modes.
4. Run simulations: Run the simulations multiple times with different population density scenarios to see how the transportation system performs under different conditions. You can use MATLAB to visualize the results and analyze the impact of population density on transportation efficiency and accessibility.
